tweet:
Saddened to learn of the death of former Congressman Bob Traxler. 

Jennifer and I extend our deepest condolences to Bob’s wife, Jeanine, and others who loved Bob dearly.  https://bit.ly/36gDV7P  https://twitter.com/BayCityTimes/status/1189995657127452675 …

The House will proceed with the seriousness that this moment in history demands. We will conduct a thorough and public investigation to follow the facts and uncover the extent to which @realDonaldTrump's actions have threatened our national security.
Over the last several weeks, senior White House officials, career foreign service officers and national security officials have all presented evidence of @realDonaldTrump's abuse of power.

The President, by his own admission, used his office to try and pressure a foreign government into investigating a political opponent. In doing so, @realDonaldTrump endangered our national security by withholding critical military assistance for his own personal gain.

No Member of Congress was elected to begin impeachment proceedings. But I took an oath of office to protect and defend the Constitution, and I believe that we must proceed in uncovering the extent to which @RealDonaldTrump has abused his power and betrayed his oath of office.
Opening an impeachment inquiry against the President of the United States should always be a tool of last resort, but sadly this is a necessary step to uphold and defend our Constitution.

Throughout his life, John Conyers helped to advance many important causes, including expanding voting rights and equal rights for all Americans. Jennifer and I extend our condolences to John's family during this difficult time.

John Conyers was a fighter for civil rights who served the people of Detroit in Congress for over 50 years. As a founding member of @TheBlackCaucus, John Conyers rose to become the longest-serving African American in Congress and Dean of the House.

The death of al-Baghdadi is a major accomplishment, but it does not mean that ISIS is defeated. We must remain vigilant. America must have a comprehensive strategy, working with our allies, to root out ISIS terrorists that still pose a threat to our national security.

To those who supported the operation that killed ISIS leader Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi, including American special forces, our Kurdish allies, the @CIA and our intelligence officers, thank you for bringing this barbaric terrorist to justice.

Let's be clear—what my GOP colleagues did this week to disrupt order wasn't some heroic March on Washington. It was a publicity stunt.

Their greatest allegiance isn't to our Constitution, it's to this lawless President. History is not going to judge them well. pic.twitter.com/zrmgZ5p4fW

The U.S. House just passed H. Res. 552, a bipartisan resolution calling on Russia to release Michigan-native Paul Whelan. Russia has detained Paul for 10 months without evidence and denied him consular services. Paul’s health is failing and he needs to come home immediately.

Sadly, @EPAAWheeler's visit to Michigan today is trying to mask the Trump Administration’s terrible environmental record. It takes a lot of nerve to fly into Michigan and celebrate #GreatLakes programs that the Trump Administration previously tried to eliminate.

Just recently, Trump’s @EPA announced a weak revision of the Lead and Copper Rule, which would allow lead pipes to remain in our drinking water systems, even after dangerous levels of lead have been found.
The Trump Administration repealed the Clean Water Rule, which is a handout to corporate polluters that increases pollution in the #GreatLakes.
.@RealDonaldTrump's own budget nearly eliminated the #GreatLakes Restoration Initiative, slashing funding by 90 percent to protect Michigan’s water from invasive species.
Let's remember the Trump Administration and @EPAAWheeler's terrible record when it comes to protecting clean water and our environment:

.@EPAAWheeler is in Michigan today celebrating #GreatLakes protection programs. But actions speak louder than words—the President and the Trump Administration have repeatedly tried to eliminate these same initiatives in past years.

Governor Milliken lived a life of service as a World War II veteran, an elected official, and our state's longest-serving Governor. Compromise was never a dirty word for him. He was a kind soul and served our state with conviction, compassion and a sense of civility. https://twitter.com/freep/status/1185315988402778112 …

Our nation has lost a true warrior. Elijah Cummings was a defender of democracy and champion for justice, including giving a voice to the people of my hometown of Flint. He could roar like a lion and brought moral clarity and purpose to all his work. I will miss my friend dearly. pic.twitter.com/A6jKdqlQoY

I am glad to see Congress, in a bipartisan fashion, condemn the President’s recent foreign policy decisions. @RealDonaldTrump's abandonment of our Kurdish partners in Syria sends a chilling message to every other American ally across the globe. https://twitter.com/BreakingNews/status/1184554390998441984 …
.@UAW workers deserve a fair shake from @GM that includes good wages, strong health care, job security and a commitment from the company to make their vehicles in America.

A proposed tentative agreement between @GM and the @UAW is a positive step forward. 

I respect the hardworking men and women of the United Auto Workers, who will make the final decision on whether or not to ratify their contract.

We must hold the Defense Department accountable for #PFAS chemical contamination. 

That's why I'm pleased that the DOD Inspector General has initiated a review of the department's use of these dangerous chemicals at military sites. https://bit.ly/2Bhbnws

.@realDonaldTrump released his Lead and Copper Rule today, an extreme step backward in the fight to protect public health. His rule doesn't lower the action level for lead & allows lead pipes to remain in communities, even after high levels of lead have been found in water. https://twitter.com/washingtonpost/status/1182317805078794241 …

Bill White has had an incredible impact on our community that will be felt for generations. His intellect and big heart were always focused on improving the lives of people less fortunate and bettering the lives of Michigan's children and families. We will miss him dearly. https://twitter.com/MLive/status/1182016410559619073 …

Back on the picket line this morning in Swartz Creek supporting @UAW workers. Workers deserve a fair shake—good wages, decent health care and a commitment from @GM to make their vehicles in America. I stand in solidarity with workers on strike across our district and the country. pic.twitter.com/EzvcjlZs8M

Today the Supreme Court will determine the future of LGBTQ protections in the workplace. No one should be fired from the job because of who they are.

I joined over 150 lawmakers in signing a brief to protect LGBTQ Americans & will always fight for equality for all. #TitleVII pic.twitter.com/Jgce125Rfo
House Democrats can walk and chew gum at the same time. We've passed important legislation that the American people have long wanted action on, while also holding this lawless President accountable.

H.R. 582, the Raise the Wage Act, which would increase the paychecks of all American workers by gradually increasing the federal minimum wage to $15 an hour by 2025.  https://bit.ly/30Vtxi1  #FightFor15
H.R. 2722, the SAFE Act, which strengthens America’s election infrastructure and protects voters from potential hacking and the manipulation of votes. https://bit.ly/2Orb7D0
H.R. 6, the American Dream and Promise Act, which provides a path to lawful permanent resident status, and eventual citizenship, for DREAMers. https://bit.ly/2nidFYS

H.R. 1994, the SECURE Act, which makes it easier for workers to save for retirement and invests in apprenticeship programs that help people get the training and skills they need for high-wage jobs. https://bit.ly/338UbVX
H.R. 1644, the Save the Internet Act, which restores #NetNeutrality protections, ensuring that the internet is open to all Americans and free from interference. https://bit.ly/2GfS0r2

H.R. 7, the Paycheck Fairness Act, which strengthens and closes loopholes in existing law, including the 1963 Equal Pay Act, to help ensure that women and men get paid the same if they are doing the same work. https://bit.ly/2oVXQaO
H.R. 9, which requires the Trump Administration to remain in the Paris Climate Accord so that we can combat climate change. https://bit.ly/2LOl23Q

H.R. 5, the Equality Act, which ensures that all Americans—including LGBT Americans—would be protected from discrimination in employment, housing, credit, education, public spaces and services, federally funded programs, and jury service. https://bit.ly/338ifbo
H.R. 987, which begins to rein in the soaring costs of health care and prescription drugs for working families and seniors. https://bit.ly/33276ZI

H.R. 1585, which reauthorizes the Violence Against Women Act to end instances of domestic violence, dating violence, sexual assault and stalking, and funds local programs to support victims. https://bit.ly/2IjIjcx

H.R. 986, which helps to protect families from predatory junk insurance plans that do not offer comprehensive health care coverage, including coverage for pre-existing conditions. https://bit.ly/2LRMkX0
H.R. 8, which would close dangerous loopholes and require background checks for all gun sales. https://bit.ly/2MdpWGA
H.R. 1, which would end the role of big money in politics, expand voting rights and ensure that public officials work for the people, not special interests. https://bit.ly/2UmpMzs

In the real world, this is not OK. @realDonaldTrump cannot distract us from his corrupt actions that betrayed his oath of office.
